India Extends Stock-Holding Rule for Sugar Traders by 2 Months

-- B y   P r a t i k   P a r i j a
-- 
2011-09-30T07:47:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/india-extends-stock-holding-rule-for-sugar-traders-by-2-months.html
India  extended a rule that governs
the stock-holding limit for sugar traders by two months to Nov.
30, 2011, the food ministry said in a statement in  New Delhi 
today.  Traders are allowed to hold as much as 500 metric tons of
the sweetener for a month, the ministry said. The stockpile rule
was earlier valid until Sept. 30.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Pratik Parija at 
 pparija@bloomberg.net  